   139→## Versions
   141→A "version" is described by the `v2.0.0` specification found at
   142→<https://semver.org/>.
   143→
   144→A leading `"="` or `"v"` character is stripped off and ignored.
   145→Support for stripping a leading "v" is kept for compatibility with `v1.0.0` of the SemVer
   146→specification but should not be used anymore.
   147→
   148→## Ranges
   150→A `version range` is a set of `comparators` that specify versions
   151→that satisfy the range.
   152→
   153→A `comparator` is composed of an `operator` and a `version`.  The set
   154→of primitive `operators` is:
   155→
   156→* `<` Less than
   157→* `<=` Less than or equal to
   158→* `>` Greater than
   159→* `>=` Greater than or equal to
   160→* `=` Equal.  If no operator is specified, then equality is assumed,
   161→  so this operator is optional but MAY be included.
   162→
   163→For example, the comparator `>=1.2.7` would match the versions
   164→`1.2.7`, `1.2.8`, `2.5.3`, and `1.3.9`, but not the versions `1.2.6`
   165→or `1.1.0`. The comparator `>1` is equivalent to `>=2.0.0` and
   166→would match the versions `2.0.0` and `3.1.0`, but not the versions
   167→`1.0.1` or `1.1.0`.
   168→
   169→Comparators can be joined by whitespace to form a `comparator set`,
      →…
   184→### Prerelease Tags
   219→#### Prerelease Identifiers
   250→#### Prerelease Identifier Base
   279→### Advanced Range Syntax
   287→#### Hyphen Ranges `X.Y.Z - A.B.C`
   306→#### X-Ranges `1.2.x` `1.X` `1.2.*` `*`
   324→#### Tilde Ranges `~1.2.3` `~1.2` `~1`
   341→#### Caret Ranges `^1.2.3` `^0.2.5` `^0.0.4`
   384→### Range Grammar
   408→## Functions
   410→All methods and classes take a final `options` object argument.  All
   411→options in this object are `false` by default.  The options supported
   412→are:
   413→
   414→- `loose`: Be more forgiving about not-quite-valid semver strings.
   415→  (Any resulting output will always be 100% strict compliant, of
   416→  course.)  For backwards compatibility reasons, if the `options`
   417→  argument is a boolean value instead of an object, it is interpreted
   418→  to be the `loose` param.
   419→- `includePrerelease`: Set to suppress the [default
   420→  behavior](https://github.com/npm/node-semver#prerelease-tags) of
   421→  excluding prerelease tagged versions from ranges unless they are
   422→  explicitly opted into.
   423→
   424→Strict-mode Comparators and Ranges will be strict about the SemVer
   425→strings that they parse.
   426→
   427→* `valid(v)`: Return the parsed version, or null if it's not valid.
   428→* `inc(v, releaseType, options, identifier, identifierBase)`: 
   429→  Return the version incremented by the release
      →  …
